ADDITIONAL TERMS AND CONDITIONS
===============================================================================

The following terms supplement the GPL v3.0 and clarify obligations for
redistributors while ensuring users are informed about the alpha status.

1. MANDATORY ATTRIBUTION & COPYRIGHT NOTICE
   ─────────────────────────────────────────
   
   When redistributing the software (source or binary), you must include the
   following attribution exactly as shown in an obvious place (README, About
   page, documentation, etc.):
   
   Based on NEURO (https://github.com/PanzerPeter/Neuro) — 
   Copyright (C) 2024–2025 NEURO Project Contributors
   
   You must also preserve:
   • All existing copyright notices
   • The ALPHA VERSION NOTICE
   • The full text of this supplementary section

2. MANDATORY ALPHA NOTICE IN DISTRIBUTIONS
   ───────────────────────────────────────
   
   Any redistribution (source or binary) must include:
   • The ALPHA VERSION NOTICE verbatim
   • A prominent statement in user-facing materials that the software is an
     alpha release and may be unstable

3. MODIFICATION DOCUMENTATION
   ──────────────────────────
   
   If you distribute a modified version, you must:
   • Clearly mark modified files and distributions as modified
   • Include a CHANGES or MODIFICATIONS file summarizing changes, authors,
     and modification dates
   • Not misrepresent the modified version as the original NEURO project

4. SOURCE PROVISION FOR BINARIES
   ─────────────────────────────
   
   If distributing compiled/binary forms, you must:
   • Comply with GPL v3.0 source offer requirements
   • Include a prominent pointer to where complete source may be obtained

5. TRADEMARK AND ENDORSEMENT RESTRICTIONS
   ──────────────────────────────────────
   
   No permission is granted to use:
   • The NEURO Project name or trademark
   • Project logos
   • Contributor names
   
   For endorsement or promotion without explicit written permission.

6. SAFETY-CRITICAL USES (ADVISORY)
   ───────────────────────────────
   
   This software has not been tested for safety-critical deployments. You are
   strongly advised NOT to use this software in:
   • Medical or life-support systems
   • Aviation or nuclear applications
   • Other environments where failures could cause injury, death, or severe
     property/environmental damage

7. CONTRIBUTION GUIDELINES (REQUEST)
   ─────────────────────────────────
   
   Contributors are requested (but not legally required) to:
   • Report security vulnerabilities or serious bugs via:
     https://github.com/PanzerPeter/Neuro/issues
   • Submit improvements as pull requests with clear descriptions

8. LICENSE TERMINATION
   ───────────────────
   
   Failure to comply with the GPL or these terms terminates license rights.
   Rights may be reinstated as provided in GPL v3.0.

